  "type": "mcq",
  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Students think that because an entrepreneur has all four characteristics, their business is guaranteed to succeed.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Having the right characteristics increases the chance of success but does not guarantee it. Market conditions, competition, economic factors, and access to finance all affect whether a business succeeds. The examiner expects you to consider multiple factors when evaluating.</p>",
  "question": "Does having all four entrepreneurial characteristics guarantee that a business will succeed?",
