  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Once a business becomes a plc, it must remain a plc permanently.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Some businesses that became plcs have chosen to return to being private limited companies ('going private'). This can happen when owners want to regain control, protect themselves from hostile takeovers, or reduce the costs and public scrutiny associated with being a plc.</p>",
