  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Market share and profit are the same thing.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Market share is the percentage of total market sales held by a business. A business can have a high market share but low profit (e.g., if it has cut prices to gain customers). They are related but different concepts with different formulas.</p>",
