  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Customers only care about getting the cheapest price.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Customers care about the overall value they receive — which includes price, product quality, customer service, availability, product range and convenience. In specific contexts, some customers prioritise quality or ethics over price (e.g. choosing ethically-sourced products). Always link customer objectives to the specific business context in the case study.</p>",
