  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Students often write that the purpose of marketing is 'to make a profit' or 'to increase profit'.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> The principal role of marketing is to INCREASE SALES, not profit directly. The examiner mark scheme specifically states that 'increase sales' is the correct answer. Profit may result from higher sales, but profit is not the primary purpose of the marketing function — and reducing the price to increase sales could even reduce profit.</p>",
  "question": "According to the exam mark scheme, what is the principal role of marketing?",
