  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> For 'analyse' questions about market segmentation, students often answer by describing what segmentation is, instead of analysing its benefit or impact on the business.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Explaining WHAT segmentation is scores zero for 'analyse' or 'explain' questions. You need: Understanding of a benefit (1) → Application to the named business (1) → Business impact/Analysis (1). E.g. 'Segmentation allows Sainsbury's to alter products to satisfy the specific needs of middle to high income customers (U+APP), which will help boost revenue and maintain customer loyalty in a very competitive supermarket industry (AN).'</p>",
