  "type": "mcq",
  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> For 'analyse' questions about product development and segmentation, students often mention pricing, advertising or promotion rather than the product itself.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> If the question asks about market segmentation when DEVELOPING NEW PRODUCTS, your answer must focus on the PRODUCT — e.g. how segmentation helps the business create, design, tailor or alter the product to meet the needs of specific customer groups. Do NOT answer with points about pricing, advertising, or launching the product — these are post-development and will not be credited.</p>",
  "question": "When a question asks how market segmentation helps with DEVELOPING NEW PRODUCTS, what must the answer focus on?",
