  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Students assume that a product-orientated business will always fail because they don't do market research first.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> While riskier, product-orientated businesses can be massively successful if they create a highly innovative product that consumers didn't even know they wanted yet (e.g., the first smartphones or early tech inventions).</p>",
