  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Students think 'Integrated Marketing Mix' means spending exactly the same amount of money on all 4 Ps.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Integration has nothing to do with budget equality. It means the 4 Ps send a CONSISTENT MESSAGE. A high-end product needs a high price, an exclusive place, and premium promotion.</p>",
  "question": "What does an 'Integrated Marketing Mix' actually require?",
