  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> In 9-mark questions about market data, students just copy numbers from the table without manipulating them.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> To score high analysis marks, you MUST manipulate the data. Don't just say 'Sales went from 120k to 145k'. Say 'Sales increased by 25,200, which is a 21% increase, but the market grew by 44%'. Calculate the differences!</p>",
