  "readingTitle": "Analysis Trick — The Market Data Trap",
  "reading": "<p>If an exam question gives you a table showing a business's sales increasing, immediately check the 'Total Market' figures.</p>\n  <p>Examiners love to trick you into saying \"the business is doing well because sales are up\". If the total market is growing faster than the business, their market share is dropping, which is a massive <strong>negative</strong> point for analysis.</p>",
