  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> HR planning is too expensive and time-consuming to be worthwhile.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> While HR planning does have a cost (time and money), the BENEFITS usually outweigh these costs. Without planning, a business may recruit too many workers (wasting wages) or too few (failing to meet demand). Good HR planning helps the business be efficient and competitive — it is time and money well spent.</p>",
