   "markScheme": "<div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Answer</h5><p><strong>A — every £100 of sales earns £1.30 less net profit than it used to</strong></p></div><div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Examiner's Comment</h5><p>This was the least well answered question in the whole paper. If the margin falls from 4.2% to 2.9%, that is a fall of 1.3 pence per pound, so £1.30 for each £100.</p><ul><li>Answer C was the most common wrong answer — a fall from 4.2% to 2.9% is actually a decrease of 31%, not 1.3%</li><li>Answer D was also popular — but the margin remains positive, so a profit is still being made</li></ul></div>",
