  "caseStudy": "A furniture maker intends to purchase a new wood cutting machine:\n• Cost of machine: £6,000\n• Income Year 1: £3,000\n• Income Year 2: £3,000\n• Income Year 3: £3,000",
  "hint": "Total profit = total income − cost. Average annual profit = total profit ÷ years. ARR = (average annual profit ÷ cost) × 100.",
  "starter": "The ARR is calculated by first working out total profit over the machine's life...",
