  "num": "Q46biii",
  "question": "Analyse one change in SP's dry cleaning chemical costs between 2017 and 2018. Refer to Pie charts 1 and 2 in your answer. [3 marks]",
  "hint": "Use both pie charts to calculate the actual cost in pounds for dry cleaning chemicals in each year. Then compare the change and explain what it means for SP.",
  "starter": "SP's dry cleaning chemical costs changed between 2017 and 2018 because...",
  "key": {
   "markScheme": "<div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Mark Allocation (AO2 + AO3a = 3 marks)</h5><ul><li><strong>1 mark:</strong> Applying information from Pie charts 1 and 2 to SP (using actual figures)</li><li><strong>2 marks:</strong> Analysing the change in SP's spending on dry cleaning chemicals</li><li>Analysis marks can come from two separate effects OR development of one effect</li></ul></div><div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Application may include:</h5><ul><li>2017: 20% × £4,400 = £880/month (£10,560/year)</li><li>2018: 20% × £5,500 = £1,100/month (£13,200/year)</li><li>Increase of £220/month or £2,640/year</li></ul></div><div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Analysis may include:</h5><ul><li>Costs increased by £220/month, however the proportion of all variable costs stayed the same (both 20%)</li><li>May be due to more sales, leading SP to purchase more chemicals</li><li>May be due to the cost of chemicals increasing</li></ul></div><div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Examiner's Comment</h5><p>The dry cleaning chemical proportion stayed at 20%, but the actual value increased by £220/month. Many candidates lacked analysis of what this change meant for the business.</p></div>",
   "modelAnswer": "The dry cleaning chemical costs increased from £880/month in 2017 to £1,100/month in 2018 (APP), an increase of £220 per month. However, as a proportion of total variable costs they stayed the same at 20% (AN). This may be because SP is serving more customers and therefore needs more chemicals (AN)."
  }
