   "markScheme": "<div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Mark Allocation (AO3b = 3 marks)</h5><ul><li><strong>1 mark:</strong> A judgement — recommend HD Sewing OR Fast Stitch</li><li><strong>1 further mark:</strong> Justification for the judgement</li><li><strong>1 further mark:</strong> Use of context within the justification (reference to data from Table 1)</li><li>All 3 marks are for evaluation only — no marks for other skill areas</li><li>No reward for 'sitting on the fence'</li></ul></div><div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Examiner's Comment</h5><p>Most candidates made a recommendation. The most common argument for HD was higher net profit per year; the most common argument for Fast Stitch was the lower purchase price. Figures needed to be referenced but did not need to be quoted exactly. The command word 'recommend' requires a decision to be made.</p></div>",
   "modelAnswer": "<strong>Model Answer 1 (Fast Stitch):</strong> It is clear that SP should buy Fast Stitch (1) because Pippa is more concerned about the return on her investment within five years (1) and Fast Stitch has the higher ARR of 13.8% (1).<br><br><strong>Model Answer 2 (HD Sewing):</strong> SP should buy HD Sewing (1) because Stuart and Pippa as business owners want to make as much profit as possible (1) and HD has the higher annual net profit of £25,000 (1)."
