  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Part-time workers have fewer employment rights than full-time workers.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Part-time employees have EXACTLY THE SAME employment rights as full-time workers. The number of hours worked does not affect the type or permanency of their employment rights. This is a very common misconception that loses marks.</p>",
