  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Flexible/home working is always beneficial for both businesses and workers.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Flexible/home working has BOTH benefits and drawbacks for BOTH parties. For workers: benefits include saving travel costs and flexibility, but drawbacks include social isolation and home distractions. For businesses: benefits include reduced office costs and productivity gains, but drawbacks include monitoring difficulties and technology costs. Never state it is 'always good.'</p>",
