  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> The chain of command and the span of control are the same concept.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> They are different. The CHAIN OF COMMAND is the LINE of authority from top to bottom (vertical path of instructions). The SPAN OF CONTROL is the NUMBER of subordinates one manager has (horizontal count). Confusing these terms in exam answers loses marks.</p>",
  "question": "What is the key difference between chain of command and span of control?",
