  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> 'Recruitment' and 'selection' mean the same thing.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> They are different stages. Recruitment refers to searching for suitable candidates and attracting them to apply for a vacancy. Selection refers to the process of vetting candidates to choose the most suitable person for the role.</p>",
