  "type": "mcq",
  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> A job description lists the qualifications and skills needed for the job.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> A job description lists the tasks, duties and responsibilities of the role. Qualifications and skills needed belong in the person specification. Confusing these two documents is one of the most common errors in GCSE exams.</p>",
