  "type": "mcq",
  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Internal recruitment is always better because it is cheaper.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Internal recruitment has advantages (cheaper, quicker, motivated staff) but also disadvantages (no fresh ideas, limited choice, causes conflict). The best method depends on the specific situation — for example, if a business needs a skills gap filled, external recruitment is needed.</p>",
  "question": "Why is it wrong to say internal recruitment is 'always better' than external recruitment?",
