  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Employee retention is important just because it makes workers feel good.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Examiners want business-focused reasons. Retention reduces recruitment and training costs (which can be 50–60% of annual salary), maintains expertise and customer relationships, supports morale, and makes the business more attractive to future recruits.</p>",
