  "type": "mcq",
  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Apprenticeships are only for school leavers looking for their first job.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> On this specification, apprenticeships are a form of staff development for existing employees. They reduce the time a worker spends on their normal duties while they study — they are not just a cheap way to recruit new workers.</p>",
