  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> The Statement of Employment Particulars IS the contract of employment.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> They are different things. The contract is the legal agreement (formed verbally or in writing). The statement is a written document that records the main terms of that contract. Students often mix these up in exams.</p>",
