  "type": "mcq",
  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Flow production workers are highly skilled.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Flow production workers typically carry out repetitive, specialised tasks on an assembly line and are generally not considered highly skilled. It is JOB production that requires skilled workers — craftspeople, architects, surgeons, etc. — which is why job production has higher labour costs.</p>",
  "question": "Which production method requires the most skilled workers, and why?",
