  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Flow production always produces lower quality goods compared to job production.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Flow production CAN produce high-quality, consistent goods. Modern computer-controlled machines are highly accurate. Cars produced on assembly lines, for example, undergo rigorous quality checks. The assumption that mass-produced automatically means low quality is outdated and incorrect.</p>",
  "question": "Does flow production necessarily produce lower quality goods than job production?",
