  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Students write that 'an online business doesn't need to think about location at all.'</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Online businesses still have critical location decisions — particularly for their warehouses. They need good transport links (road/rail), a reliable labour supply, and affordable land. The Wool Warehouse is a clear example of deliberate location planning for an online business.</p>",
  "question": "What location factor is MOST important for an online retailer choosing where to put its warehouse?",
