  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Students think 'Silicon Fen' is in Silicon Valley, USA.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Silicon Fen is an area near Cambridge, UK. It is named after the Fens (the flat marshy land near Cambridge). It is a cluster of ICT firms and highly skilled technology workers, not connected to Silicon Valley in California.</p>",
  "question": "Where is 'Silicon Fen' and why is it relevant to business location?",
