   "modelAnswer": "A disadvantage is that the old machines may not sell for enough money to cover the full cost of the new machinery (U). RCP needs over £100,000, but second-hand laser cutters and 3D printers may not attract buyers quickly or at the right price (APP). If the sale falls short of the target, RCP will need to raise additional finance from elsewhere, wasting time and potentially delaying the upgrade, which could harm their production capacity (AN)."
