   "markScheme": "<div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Answer: A — 68%</h5><ul><li><strong>Working:</strong> Revenue = 42 × £350 = £14,700. GPM = (£9,996 ÷ £14,700) × 100 ≈ 68%.</li><li><strong>Why B is wrong:</strong> 147% would only be possible if gross profit exceeded revenue — impossible.</li><li><strong>Why C is wrong:</strong> £4,704 is the cost of sales (£14,700 − £9,996) — not a gross profit margin.</li><li><strong>Why D is wrong:</strong> £14,700 is the total revenue — not a gross profit margin.</li></ul><p><strong>Examiner's Comment:</strong> Students who knew a GPM must be a percentage could immediately eliminate C and D. Only A and B are percentages, and 147% exceeding 100% for a GPM is unrealistic.</p></div>",
