  "starter": "One limitation is that the data used in break-even analysis are only estimates... (U)\nFor GK, the variable cost of £6,380 or the selling price of £15,000 could change if... (APP)\nThis means GK may need to... (AN)",
  "key": {
   "markScheme": "<div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Mark Allocation — 3 marks (AO1b + AO2 + AO3a)</h5><p><strong>Understanding (1 mark) — limitations include:</strong></p><ul><li>All data in break-even is estimated / a prediction</li><li>The number of competitors may change</li><li>The business may make promotional offers at a lower price</li><li>Costs may change unexpectedly</li><li>External economic factors may change</li><li>Qualitative / non-financial issues are not considered</li></ul><p><strong>Application (1 mark) — specific reference to GK:</strong></p><ul><li>GK's variable cost of £6,380 per kitchen / price of £15,000</li><li>GK sells high-quality luxury kitchens — demand is sensitive to income changes</li><li>Forecast fall in consumer incomes across the south-east</li><li>Unemployment forecast to fall from 4.0% to 3.1% (suggesting more potential customers)</li></ul><p><strong>Analysis (1 mark):</strong></p><ul><li>GK may need to adjust its prices or costs to overcome uncertainty in the data</li><li>Sales targets may need to be constantly revised as circumstances change</li><li>A price cut to stimulate demand may not lead to an increase in revenue if demand is inelastic</li></ul><p><strong>⚠️ Zero marks for:</strong> Answers suggesting the data is \"wrong\" or \"inaccurate\" — this does not show understanding of WHY or HOW it could be inaccurate.</p><p><strong>Examiner's Comment:</strong> Fewer than half of candidates gained at least 1 mark. Most correct answers noted data was estimated, but then failed to apply this to GK's specific context or analyse the resulting impact on the business.</p></div>",
   "modelAnswer": "GK's suppliers of wood may increase their prices, raising the variable cost above the £6,380 per kitchen currently assumed (U+APP). As GK makes luxury Deluxe kitchens, even a modest rise in material costs could significantly increase the break-even output above 29 — forcing GK to revise its sales targets upward or consider raising its price at a time when consumer incomes in the south-east are already forecast to fall (AN)."
  }
