   "modelAnswer": "One use of a cash flow forecast is to anticipate periods of cash shortage (1). For RCP, whose overdraft is growing each month, this would allow Alessia and Natalia to identify in advance when cash may run out, so they can arrange additional finance (such as a loan) before the shortage becomes a crisis (1)."
