   "markScheme": "<div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Answer: C — £7,505 (1 mark, AO2)</h5><p><strong>Calculation:</strong> Total Outflow = Total Inflow − Net Cash Flow = £6,900 − (−£605) = £6,900 + £605 = <strong>£7,505</strong>.</p><p><strong>Verification:</strong> Closing = Opening + Net = £3,000 + (−£605) = £2,395 ✓</p><p><strong>Why others are wrong:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>A — £3,900:</strong> No logical basis.</li><li><strong>B — £6,295:</strong> Subtracts £605 from £6,900 without considering the sign, giving £6,295 instead of adding.</li><li><strong>D — £9,295:</strong> Adds £6,900 + £3,000 - £605, mixing up different rows incorrectly.</li></ul></div>",
