   "markScheme": "<div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Mark Allocation (AO1a + AO1b = 2 marks)</h5><ul><li><strong>1 mark:</strong> Identifying an advantage of operating as a multinational</li><li><strong>+1 mark:</strong> Explaining why it is an advantage for the business</li><li>Answers must apply to the business, not to the host country</li><li>No reward for answers that are simply an advantage of a business growing in general</li><li>Answer does not need to apply to Barclays plc</li></ul></div><div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Acceptable Answers include:</h5><ul><li>The ability to source labour cheaply → helping to maximise profit</li><li>Access to a larger number of customers → leading to increased sales / market share</li><li>Spreading risk by increasing sales in one country if another is in decline</li><li>Taking advantage of different tax regimes → helping to reduce costs / increase retained profit</li></ul></div>",
