   "markScheme": "<div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Answer</h5><p><strong>D — take account of cultural differences</strong></p></div><div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Why the other options are wrong</h5><ul><li><strong>A is wrong</strong> — Advertising online is just one communication channel. A business can have a strong international brand without advertising online, and online advertising is not a defining requirement of international branding.</li><li><strong>B is wrong</strong> — Ignoring religious differences would actively damage a brand internationally. Successful international branding requires sensitivity to both cultural AND religious differences, not ignoring them.</li><li><strong>C is wrong</strong> — A business does not need to sell in every single country to develop an international brand. International branding is about creating a consistent global image; a business could operate in just a handful of countries and still have an international brand.</li></ul></div>",
